11 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Department of
Emergency Management; appropriating certain funds in
12 certain amount for certain purpose; directing
utilization of certain amounts for certain purposes;
13 providing for noncodification; providing an effective
date; and declaring an emergency.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
18 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
19 There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Department of
20 Emergency Management from any monies not otherwise appropriated from
21 the General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for the fiscal year
22 ending June 30, 2027, the sum of One Million Dollars ($1,000,000.00)
23 or so much thereof as may be necessary to perform the duties imposed
24 upon the Oklahoma Department of Emergency Management by law.
Req. No. 17380 Page 1

1 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
2 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
3 Funds appropriated by Section 1 of this act shall be utilized as
4 follows:
5 One Million Dollars ($1,000,000.00) to be transferred to the
6 Oklahoma Task Force 1 Revolving Fund created by Enrolled House Bill
7 No. 3831 of the 2nd Session of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature.
8 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
9 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
10 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
11 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
12 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
